default3.1
default              
defaultDigital technologies are transforming our society, economy and culture.  In the past, spectrum as the
default means of linear distribution was scarce, and making content was inherently expensive.
default&#xa0;
default3.2
default              
defaultNow many more people can create and share their own content, including   ar
defaulttists and arts organisations. This has been demonstrated by the National Theatre
default Royal Opera House and British Museum winning large audiences of their own in cinemas
default both
default here and around the world. 
default&#xa0;
default3.3
default              
defaultFor the BBC, the digital era offers new opportunities to refresh its mission to inform, to educate and to entertain. As Tony Hall ha
defaults said: “The key challenge - the core of what we have to do - is to harness our power to create - our power to innovate”
default.  But it is also an opportunity to amplify, to connect and to support a far wider network of content providers, distributors and audie
defaultnces. With public expenditure rightly under more scrutiny than ever before, it is vital that the BBC works in partnership with a wider variety of organisations and individuals to fulfil its public service obligations. 
defaultWe are entering a different era and thdefaulte BBC’s role is now to engage with it and enable it.default&#xa0;
default3.4
default              
defaultIn a pressured public funding environment, the BBC should maintain its strong leadership role and scale of investment in key areas of its cultural and educational remit, and in ensuring its continui
defaultng commitment to the breadth of cultural services across its broadcast and digital channels.
default&#xa0;
default3.5
default              
defaultBut we believe that the next big shift is that, in return for the stability of the licence fee and the ability it gives the BBC to invest in depth and scale, 
defaultit should be able to point to partnerships it has forged where, most often, the result is a whole that adds up to more than the sum of the parts. This will enable the licence fee to be much more dynamic, providing a greater return than if it had simply bee
defaultn spent exclusively within the BBC
default,
default and works with investment from other sources. 
default&#xa0;
default3.6
default              
defaultIn 2014, the BBC and Arts Council will sign a new three year 
defaultp
defaultartnership agreement. Through this partnership we aim to provide a stronger and more effective interface between the BBC, the Arts Council and arts and cultural organisations and artists throughout England to increase the value, reach and impact of public 
defaultinvestment in arts, culture and the BBC, to identify new talent and new work, to support training and talent and progression routes in regional centres such as Bristol, Birmingham and Salford and to use digital technologies to better connect publicly funde
defaultd arts content with audiences through BBC services and platforms, including the development of The Space. 
default&#xa0;
