default4.2
default              
defaultThe core financial model and constitution of the BBC allows it to be funded without political interference and stresses the prima
defaultcy of independent operation and commissioning. This has proven to be a hugely valuable and successful model, and any diminution would be undesirable. 
default&#xa0;
default4.3
default              
defaultThe BBC must be accountable to licence-fee payers, as the Arts Council should be to tax-payers – but
default the arms-length principle is vitally important, as is the ability to set its own budget. It is this which allows proper independence for decisions to be taken free from political pressure, real or perceived.
default&#xa0;
default4.
default4
default              
defaultWhile the BBC should be alive to the context in which it operates, decisions on operations and commissioning should be made independently. There has 
defaulthistorically been a broad consensus that this is beyond question, and it should remain so. Such independenc
defaulte constitutes a fundamental tenet of the values underpinning public service broadcasting, and is especially important in the fields of arts and culture.  In making the case for the continuation of the licence fee, the BBC should be bold and clear about the
default role of a Public Service Broadcaster in the 21st century, and restate and reanimate the Reithian ideals on which it is founded. 
